Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane has given an update on the province's efforts to combat coronavirus. Courtesy #DStv403  EAST LONDON - Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane said the COVID-19 curve is flattening in the province. He said there's been a consistent decline in the number of new daily infections. WATCH: Eastern Cape COVID-19 update Mabuyane said although the COVID-19 storm is not over yet, its end might be closer than expected. The province's recovery rate is nearing 94 percent. He said 85 healthcare workers have succumbed to COVID-19 in the province. COVID-19 in SA: Eastern Cape's shortcomings The premier said 466 deaths have been confirmed within a matter of nine days in the province due to COVID-19. He sent condolences to all those who lost a loved one because of the virus. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.